article.headline: Illinois State 69, SMS 57
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Blake Ahearn had 17 points and made his 54th straight free throw as Southwest Missouri State beat Illinois State 69-57 Saturday night. Ahearn, who had eight free throws, broke the 5-year-old Missouri Valley Conference record of 48 consecutive free throws in the first half. The Bears (15-8, 7-5 MVC) opened the second half cold, making just one field goal in the first 6:54 and only three in the first 10 minutes. But Ahearn made four straight free throws in the early part of the half to keep Illinois State (6-14, 2-10) from closing in. The Redbirds went nearly five minutes without a basket midway through the half while Southwest Missouri went on a 7-0 run. Illinois State shot 42 percent (20-of-48) from the field, while the Bears shot 53 percent (21 of 40). Tyler Chaney had 12 for Southwest Missouri and Merrill Andrews added 10. Marcus Arnold led the Redbirds with 17. Trey Guidry added 11 and Vince Greene scored 10.
